â€¢ Protect sensitive environmental and visual resources at the communityâ€™s edges by establishing
effective buffers along the northern boundary with Old River, the southern boundary with I-205,
and the eastern and western boundaries with agricultural lands.
â€¢ Maintain and enhance the habitat resources of Mountain House Creek as a park and wildlife
corridor through the community.
â€¢ Minimize air quality impacts by providing for more efficient transportation systems and
